<h1>Amir Motlagh</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://www.amirmotlagh.com/now">amirmotlagh.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Los Angeles
CA
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
I'm a writer/director and founder of ANIMALS Storytelling Studios. I have an ongoing music project under MIRS.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I write stories, often direct them in a visual medium while focusing on innovation, aesthetics and humanness.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I'm a creative because communicating intangibles helps to define our communal existence, which in turn makes me feel whole. The act of nothing to something is a lifelong fascination. Contributing to a shared experience through a distributable form, whether ugly or splendid is calmness.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
We have a subjective map of the world that guides are views and decisions, and defines our identity. But our identity is not what makes us human. It is a changeable construct much like computer code, which begs a much more profound question.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
One that I constantly think about this year as I made a stronger effort towards interdisciplinary thinking is “ZERO TO ONE” by Peter Thiel
</p>

